                        <li>
                            <p>
                                the area of the hexagon.
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>

            </statement>
            <solution>
                
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a) " cols="2">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                The perimeter of the hexagon is:
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \text{Perimeter} =\amp \text{Length} \times 6</mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp 16 \times 6</mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp 96 \, \text{m}</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                The area of the hexagon is:
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow> \text{Area} =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times \text{Perimeter} \times  \text{apothem}</mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{1}{2} \times 96 \times 30</mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp 48 \times 30</mrow>
                                    <mrow> =\amp 1440 \, \text{m}^2</mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                This implies that, the area of the hexagon is <m>{\color{black}1440 \, \text{m}^2}</m>.
                            </p>

                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A regular hexagon has an area of <m>54 \, \text{cm}^2</m>
                    . What is its side length?
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    To find the side length of a regular hexagon given its area, we can use the formula:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \text{Area} =\amp \frac{3\sqrt{3}}{2} \times \text{s}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Given that the area is <m>54\, \text{cm}^2</m>, we set up the equation:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> 54 =\amp \frac{3\sqrt{3}}{2} \times \text{s}^2</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    To solve for <m>\text{s}</m>, we can rearrange the equation:
                </p>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow> \text{s}^2 =\amp \frac{54 \times 2}{3\sqrt{3}}</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp \frac{108}{5.196152423}</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 20.78460969</mrow>
                        <mrow> \text{s} =\amp \sqrt{20.78460969}</mrow>
                        <mrow> =\amp 4.559014114  </mrow>
                        <mrow>= \amp 4.559 \,\text{cm}</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Therefore, the side length of the regular hexagon is <m>{\color{black}4.559\, \text{cm}}</m>.
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>

